## 🔐 5-LAYER SECURITY CHECKS

### Layer 1: Command Whitelist
```
Valid: FORWARD, BACKWARD, LEFT, RIGHT, STOP, STATUS
Invalid: HACK, DELETE, EXECUTE, <any other>
Result if invalid: BLOCKED → INVALID_COMMAND logged
```

### Layer 2: Replay Attack Detection
```
Algorithm:
  hash = SHA(command + time_bucket)
  if hash == last_hash AND time < 5s:
    BLOCK → REPLAY_ATTACK logged
  else:
    update last_hash, proceed

Example:
  t=0s: FORWARD hash=ABC → stored
  t=2s: FORWARD hash=ABC → REPLAY! BLOCKED
  t=6s: FORWARD hash=XYZ → new bucket → ALLOWED
```

### Layer 3: Speed Validation
```
Valid range: 0 ≤ speed ≤ 200
Attack: speed = 9999 → BLOCKED
Attack: speed = -50  → BLOCKED
Result: SPEED_OUT_OF_RANGE logged
```

### Layer 4: Obstacle Safety
```
Front sensor reads: 15cm (< 20cm threshold)
Command received: FORWARD
ESP32 blocks: "Cannot move forward — obstacle at 15cm"
Result: UNSAFE_COMMAND logged, vehicle stays stopped
```

### Layer 5: Behavioral Anomaly Detection
```
Algorithm monitors last 10 commands:
  direction_changes = count(cmd[i] != cmd[i-1])

Normal:   FORWARD FORWARD FORWARD → 0 changes → OK
Attack:   F→L→R→B→L→F→R→B→L→R → 9 changes → BLOCKED

Also checks frequency:
  If >10 commands in 1 second → FREQUENCY_ATTACK
```

---

## 🚨 ATTACK SCENARIOS & RESPONSES

### Scenario 1: Invalid Command Attack
```
Hacker sends: {"command": "HACK_SYSTEM", "speed": 150}
ESP32 checks whitelist → NOT FOUND
Response: 403 BLOCKED — INVALID_COMMAND
Red LED flashes, buzzer beeps 2x
Logged: security_audit table
```

### Scenario 2: Replay Attack
```
Hacker captures: {"command": "FORWARD", "timestamp": 1000}
Hacker resends same packet 3 seconds later
ESP32: timestamp bucket matches → REPLAY DETECTED
Response: 403 BLOCKED — REPLAY_ATTACK
```

### Scenario 3: Speed Overflow
```
Hacker sends: {"command": "FORWARD", "speed": 9999}
ESP32: 9999 > 200 MAX_SPEED → BLOCKED
Response: 403 BLOCKED — SPEED_OUT_OF_RANGE
Vehicle does not accelerate dangerously
```

### Scenario 4: Obstacle Bypass Attempt
```
Obstacle at 10cm in front
Hacker sends: {"command": "FORWARD"}
ESP32: sensor reads 10cm < 20cm threshold → BLOCKED
Response: 403 BLOCKED — OBSTACLE_DETECTED (10cm)
Prevents collision
```

### Scenario 5: Behavioral Pattern Attack
```
Hacker sends 10 rapid direction changes in 2 seconds:
F→L→R→B→L→R→F→B→L→R
ESP32 counts: 9 direction changes ≥ 5 threshold
Response: 403 BLOCKED — BEHAVIORAL_ATTACK
Red LED ON, buzzer 3 beeps, vehicle stops
```

